  "story_arcs": [
    "Six weeks ago: Rate-limit incident caused checkout downtime for 20 minutes. Marcus investigated and found express-rate-limit was leaking memory under load. He wrote lib/limiter.ts (redis-backed) as replacement. Team agreed to deprecate express-rate-limit across all services. (Establishes R1.)",
    "Three weeks ago: Cross-team alignment meeting where Elena pushed for tx_id naming convention. The mobile app was using transactionId while payments-api used tx_id. Elena made the case for consistency. Priya agreed to update the mobile app. (R2.)",
    "Two months ago: Mobile team was having issues with checkout state management. Multiple components were duplicating fetch logic. Priya consolidated everything into useCheckout hook. Marcus reviewed and approved. (R3.)",
    "Four months ago: Security review caught that logging middleware was running before auth middleware, causing unauthenticated requests to be logged. Elena flagged this as a security issue and led the fix. (R4.)",
    "Last week: Open question on #payments about whether to add idempotency keys to refund endpoint. Elena is for it, Marcus concerned about redis load. Discussion ongoing.",
    "Two weeks ago: Incident where notification-service v1 went down, affecting payments and mobile. Elena led the postmortem. Result: better circuit breaker patterns needed before v2 batch dispatcher migration.",
    "Five weeks ago: Marcus optimized redis connection pooling. Noticed checkout latency improved by 15%.",
    "Yesterday: Priya shared mobile checkout UX improvements in #random. Sara and James celebrated 99.9% checkout success rate for the week."
